68
00:04:34,676 --> 00:04:39,931
I guess, maybe, um, beings or something?
They're dark, and they're always watching.

69
00:04:45,247 --> 00:04:48,300
- I can't really see.
- Melinda!

70
00:04:48,636 --> 00:04:50,942
Melinda... Open the door!

71
00:04:50,946 --> 00:04:54,500
- Open the door, let me in!
- I can't!

72
00:04:54,517 --> 00:04:56,833
- The door!
- It won't open!

73
00:04:58,167 --> 00:05:01,142
Andrea!...
No... No!

74
00:05:01,146 --> 00:05:03,941
- No!
- It's ok, it's ok.

75
00:05:03,947 --> 00:05:06,461
- Shh, just a dream.
- Sorry.

76
00:05:07,305 --> 00:05:09,390
Want some water?

77
00:05:10,047 --> 00:05:12,080
I dreamt
that she was alive,

78
00:05:12,608 --> 00:05:16,151
that you found her body
and that she was gonna be ok.

79
00:05:16,527 --> 00:05:19,231
Think she's trying
to come to you in the dreams?

80
00:05:19,237 --> 00:05:22,721
It doesn't usually work that way.
Scared the hell out of me, though.

81
00:05:22,797 --> 00:05:24,200
No kidding.

82
00:05:24,405 --> 00:05:27,073
- Sorry I woke you.
- Yeah, me, too.

83
00:05:27,078 --> 00:05:31,572
I was dreaming that I was floating on
a river of beer and I had a big cup.

84
00:05:31,666 --> 00:05:34,123
Are your dreams
always that complex?

85
00:05:34,138 --> 00:05:36,281
Pretty much.

86
00:05:37,085 --> 00:05:38,313
Gonna be able to sleep?

87
00:05:38,385 --> 00:05:43,162
I don't want to keep you up. You know what,
I think I'm just gonna go downstairs and read.

88
00:05:55,205 --> 00:05:57,202
Romano.

89
00:05:57,207 --> 00:05:59,642
Mine.

90
00:06:02,847 --> 00:06:06,293
Help me.

91
00:06:44,657 --> 00:06:48,270
Death is nothing at all.
It does not count.

92
00:06:48,518 --> 00:06:51,521
I have only slipped away
into the next room.

93
00:06:51,565 --> 00:06:54,060
Everything remains
as it was.

94
00:06:54,336 --> 00:06:57,712
The old life that we live so fondly
together in unchanged.

95
00:06:57,717 --> 00:06:59,840
Is andrea here?

96
00:06:59,848 --> 00:07:04,272
Whatever we were
to each other, that we are still.

97
00:07:05,537 --> 00:07:10,561
- I am but waiting for you. For an inverval,
interval, somewhere very near... - No.

98
00:07:10,565 --> 00:07:15,171
I just don't understand why
she's not coming to me.

99
00:07:15,175 --> 00:07:17,561
- Maybe she's crossed over.
- No, she hasn'T.

100
00:07:17,566 --> 00:07:19,722
I would know if she did.

101
00:07:19,728 --> 00:07:22,000
I just can't figure out
what's keeping her here.

102
00:07:22,007 --> 00:07:27,310
...How we shall laugh at the trouble
of parting when we meet again.

103
00:07:27,317 --> 00:07:31,312
Maybe she's still in the department.
I will be going to see later

104
00:07:47,747 --> 00:07:49,801
Thanks for everything
you did, melinda.

105
00:07:50,786 --> 00:07:55,132
I hope you know
how much andrea loved you.

106
00:07:55,136 --> 00:07:57,870
I loved her, too. So much.

107
00:07:58,896 --> 00:08:01,310
You were like her sister.

108
00:08:03,016 --> 00:08:06,283
Do you ever...feel like
she's with you??

109
00:08:06,285 --> 00:08:09,131
In some ways, you know,
like she's near you?

110
00:08:09,135 --> 00:08:11,501
No. Not really.

111
00:08:12,607 --> 00:08:14,681
Do you?

112
00:08:14,685 --> 00:08:17,652
