00:17:01,607 --> 00:17:03,872
a terrible shock.
Take a beat.

234
00:17:03,907 --> 00:17:05,262
Yeah, I can'T.

235
00:17:05,268 --> 00:17:08,910
- Why? - Because, if I stop
and think, I just feel so guilty.

236
00:17:09,405 --> 00:17:12,000
You know, like maybe
what happened to andrea is my fault.

237
00:17:12,318 --> 00:17:14,381
I mean, it's only because of me that
she knew about the plane.

238
00:17:14,388 --> 00:17:17,061
It's only because
of me that romano went looking for her.

239
00:17:17,078 --> 00:17:19,073
Maybe...

240
00:17:19,078 --> 00:17:22,463
Maybe... I unleashed something
that even I don't understand.

241
00:17:22,466 --> 00:17:24,640
Just do the best you can
do with what you know.

242
00:17:24,648 --> 00:17:26,782
I can't believe
that she's gone.

243
00:17:27,785 --> 00:17:31,611
I can't believe that she's not gonna
walk in this door at any minute

244
00:17:31,615 --> 00:17:34,533
with her coffee and a joke.

245
00:17:35,587 --> 00:17:40,351
I would give anything just to hear
her laugh one more time.

246
00:17:42,056 --> 00:17:44,980
She never doubted me.

247
00:17:45,647 --> 00:17:50,483
- Even for a minute. - Ok, there's
something that you should know about me.

248
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:56,203
- Ooh, uh-oh.
- Yeah. And it's gonna sound crazy.

249
00:17:56,206 --> 00:17:58,200
And I'm telling you
for 2 reasons.

250
00:17:58,206 --> 00:18:02,873
One, because I have a good feeling about
ypu. You don't seem like you're judgmental.

251
00:18:02,877 --> 00:18:06,220
- Ok...
- ok, so here it is.

252
00:18:07,038 --> 00:18:12,901
Uh, sometimes when people
die, their spirits don't leave.

253
00:18:12,907 --> 00:18:15,613
They stay earthbound
for all kinds of reasons.

254
00:18:18,797 --> 00:18:23,611
And, well... I can see those people.
Those...spirits.

255
00:18:23,616 --> 00:18:26,392
They talk to me,
I can help them.

256
00:18:28,118 --> 00:18:30,780
You should say
something soon.

257
00:18:32,568 --> 00:18:36,101
That...is... the...

258
00:18:37,537 --> 00:18:42,551
-... coolest thing I've ever heard.
- You don't think I'm nuts?

259
00:18:42,556 --> 00:18:47,921
Ooh, ahh, no more nuts
than I am.

260
00:18:47,935 --> 00:18:50,153
I mean, I buy it. I like it.
I knew you'd get it, I just knew it.

261
00:18:50,158 --> 00:18:53,762
Yeah, but you said there was another
reason that you were telling me.

262
00:18:53,767 --> 00:18:57,103
Yeah, you have a ghost
attached to you.

263
00:18:57,106 --> 00:19:00,563
I'm sorry, what?
What--where? Where?

264
00:19:02,296 --> 00:19:05,262
I thought you could see me!

265
00:19:05,266 --> 00:19:09,240
He's, uh, behind you. He's been
following you for the last 2 weeks.

266
00:19:09,247 --> 00:19:11,610
What--why?
What does he want?

267
00:19:12,238 --> 00:19:15,382
Finally!
Ok, it's like this all right--

268
00:19:15,388 --> 00:19:19,110
you don't have to shout! Just because you're
dead doesn't mean that I can't hear you.

269
00:19:19,117 --> 00:19:21,602
All right, all right, what do I know?
I thought I was talking

270
00:19:21,606 --> 00:19:23,243
from the great beyond or something.

271
00:19:23,266 --> 00:19:27,391
Anyway, the point is, I used to live
in the apartment she lives in now.

272
00:19:27,408 --> 00:19:31,062
Ah, he's an older man who used to live
in your apartment.

273
00:19:31,506 --> 00:19:33,960
Ok, please tell me he didn't die
in my apartment.

274
00:19:33,968 --> 00:19:38,051
I didn't die there. I crapped out on
a bus one day coming home.

275
00:19:38,057 --> 00:19:42,093
Heart attack.
But I digress. The point is this.

276
00:19:42,095 --> 00:19:47,561
There's a stack of pictures of my
grandson that fell behind the stove,

277
00:19:47,565 --> 00:19:52,460
and I never got around to gettin' them out,
and my daughter would love those shots.

278
00:19:52,475 --> 00:19:55,383
Oh, there's pictures of his grandson
behind your stove.

279
00:19:55,386 --> 00:19:58,883
My daughter's name is nancy howard.
She's in the phone book.

280
00:19:58,888 --> 00:20:00,870
He wants you to send the pictures
to his daughter. I have her name.

281
00:20:00,878 --> 00:20:02,510
She's in the phone book.

282
00:20:07,655 --> 00:20:09,951
Hey, you're kidding, right?

283
00:20:13,575 --> 00:20:16,992
Ok, I am so gonna
love this job.

284
00:20:35,857 --> 00:20:38,161
Andrea?

285
00:20:52,457 --> 00:20:55,482
Got here about
a half hour ago.

286
00:20:55,485 --> 00:20:57,783
My key won't turn in the lock.
I knock, but no one answers.

287
00:21:01,357 --> 00:21:03,833
Hello? Who's in there?

288
00:21:06,645 --> 00:21:08,682
Try your key again.

289
00:22:04,225 --> 00:22:06,221
Who could have
done that?

290
00:22:06,226 --> 00:22:08,620
That's sick.
I don't get it.

291
00:22:08,625 --> 00:22:13,441
The words... that name, romano.
I have no idea who that is, do you?

292
00:22:13,717 --> 00:22:17,793
- Everything just seems a bit crazy right now.
- Should I call the police?

293
00:22:17,795 --> 00:22:21,783
- If it'll make you feel better, but I don't--
- Melinda, if you know something,

294
00:22:21,785 --> 00:22:23,203
please, tell me.

295
00:22:23,977 --> 00:22:26,623
I really don't know
what's going on.

296
00:22:27,147 --> 00:22:29,203
You feel like you
could know a person...

297
00:22:30,226 --> 00:22:32,802
I mean, really know who they
are through and through?

298
00:22:32,838 --> 00:22:34,850
- I do.
- I do, too.

299
00:22:34,856 --> 00:22:37,951
And I know my sister.
I know it sounds crazy,

300
00:22:37,958 --> 00:22:42,720
but I feel like something's wrong.
Like she's not at rest somehow.

301
00:22:43,288 --> 00:22:45,383
I can't shake it.

302
00:22:47,737 --> 00:22:51,041
You probably know things weren't
always great with us.

303
00:22:51,045 --> 00:22:53,253
She told me you didn't talk
for 2 years..

304
00:22:53,258 --> 00:22:55,862
It's worse than that.

305
00:22:55,876 --> 00:22:58,413
There's somethin'
I never told her.

306
00:22:59,028 --> 00:23:01,162
Something she should
have known.

307
00:23:01,168 --> 00:23:04,602
- What?
- What difference does it make?

308
00:23:05,547 --> 00:23:08,072
It's too late.

309
00:23:14,087 --> 00:23:18,853
Andrea?
Are you here?

310
00:23:28,628 --> 00:23:30,631
Andrea?

311
00:23:32,365 --> 00:23:35,623
He told me not to believe
a thing you say.

312
00:23:35,627 --> 00:23:37,931
Romano?

313
00:23:37,935 --> 00:23:41,153
I don't want to be dead!
I shouldn't be dead!

314
00:23:42,657 --> 00:23:50,890
Please...help me. I don't want
to be here. But I deserve it.

315
00:23:50,937 --> 00:23:53,680
- No, you don't!
- What'll happen to me if I go with him?

316
00:23:53,687 --> 00:23:57,520
He'll turn you into something,
something just like him.

317
00:23:57,526 --> 00:24:03,052
- He makes me want to be with him!
-Andrea, it's all lies!
Please don't let him do it--

318
00:24:03,558 --> 00:24:06,783
- I have to go.
- Where?

319
00:24:06,785 --> 00:24:07,551
Back to the beginning.
Oh, my god.

320
00:24:09,827 --> 00:24:12,101
Andrea, please!

321
00:24:13,668 --> 00:24:16,982
- I have to go now.
- Andrea!

322
00:25:12,626 --> 00:25:15,940
- Hello.
- Hi, melinda, it's rick payne.

323
00:25:15,956 --> 00:25:18,272
Uh, I just got back
to my office.

324
00:25:18,276 --> 00:25:21,102
Is there any chance you can
come over here? Right away?

325
00:25:21,106 --> 00:25:24,182
Could this wait till morning?
It's been kind of a long night.

326
00:25:24,188 --> 00:25:27,660
Hmm. I don't know.
Maybe not.

327
00:25:28,655 --> 00:25:30,832
Ok, I'll be there
in like 15 minutes.

328
00:25:30,838 --> 00:25:33,100
Is there any chance
you'll pass a noodle parlor?

329
00:25:33,107 --> 00:25:35,333
- None.
- Fair enough.

330
00:26:07,266 --> 00:26:10,071
- when did this happen?
- Today. I'm teaching a class,

331
00:26:10,078 --> 00:26:12,011
and then I go out to
dinner--polynesian food.

332
00:26:12,195 --> 00:26:14,872
Have you ever had tongue
and papaya? I don't recommend it.

333
00:26:14,915 --> 00:26:19,203
I come back to my office to get some
books, and all this has happened.

334
00:26:19,295 --> 00:26:22,191
I--who could have done this?!
Some disgruntled janitor? No. No. No.

335
00:26:22,195 --> 00:26:25,693
Please. I don't think so.
And then--ooh-- check this out.

336
00:26:25,697 --> 00:26:27,780
Here's a drawing that i
didn't even know I had.

337
00:26:28,496 --> 00:26:31,472
- Do you know what it means?
- Yeah, sure.

338
00:26:32,286 --> 00:26:34,363
- Well?
- Oh, sorry, uh,

339
00:26:34,398 --> 00:26:38,151
basically it's a warning.
It's a dark motif favored by the incans.

340
00:26:38,155 --> 00:26:42,191
"Back off or die" being
the fundamental message.

341
00:26:42,848 --> 00:26:46,710
Who are you really? Come on, you come here
asking me some very interesting questions.

342
00:26:46,725 --> 00:26:51,280
Next thing I know, my office is redecorated.
And I'm on the wrong end of
an incan death threat.

343
00:26:51,287 --> 00:26:53,771
Look, I'm really am
just kind of a student.

344
00:26:53,775 --> 00:26:56,791
There are some things that I know and
some things that I'm trying to find out.

345
00:26:56,795 --> 00:26:58,791
Ok. That's--
that's great.

346
00:26:58,796 --> 00:27:01,812
But are you going to tell me this all
happened because of a supernatural event?

347
00:27:01,857 --> 00:27:04,693
- Yes.
- Come on! That's crap!

348
00:27:04,698 --> 00:27:07,252
Who--who sent you here?
Who put you up to this?

349
00:27:07,258 --> 00:27:09,163
Is it spiegelman from princeton,
that son of a bitch?

350
00:27:09,168 --> 00:27:11,783
Ok, the sketch that I gave you.
Did you find out anything about him?

351
00:27:11,808 --> 00:27:13,812
Oh, yeah.
I did actually.

352
00:27:13,818 --> 00:27:18,640
There's an obscure sect in algeria,
sort of a quasi devil worship...

353
00:27:19,035 --> 00:27:22,991
sort of a quasi devil worshiping group. They
use this image as the object of their reverence.

354
00:27:23,025 --> 00:27:26,323
I also found another group in morocco,
and there's another one in portugal.

355
00:27:26,926 --> 00:27:29,342
Wow.
This is amazing.

356
00:27:29,385 --> 00:27:32,261
Come here!, you maybe want
to see this.

357
00:27:36,698 --> 00:27:38,692
Is this...

358
00:27:38,698 --> 00:27:41,760
that's an american cult leader living in
Spain-- went by the name romano.

359
00:27:41,766 --> 00:27:44,052
This guy had 115 followers.

360
00:27:44,057 --> 00:27:47,513
And he convinced them all to
commit themselves to their dark sides.

361
00:27:47,556 --> 00:27:51,322
And like you were telling me that dark
spirits like souls to be angry and toxic.

362
00:27:51,326 --> 00:27:55,340
Toxic is an understatement. This guy convinced
these people to commit the ultimate dark act...

363
00:27:55,347 --> 00:27:58,143
That would assure them
a place alongside him in eternity.

364
00:27:58,145 --> 00:28:00,630
- Suicide?
- On a grand scale.

365
00:28:00,636 --> 00:28:03,223
You say you've seen
this guy recently?

366
00:28:03,226 --> 00:28:05,540
- Kinda.
- You know, that's fascinating to me,

367
00:28:05,585 --> 00:28:10,072
this happened in 1939! And romano
killed himself with all the others.

368
00:28:10,168 --> 00:28:12,163
And became
a dark spirit?

369
00:28:12,165 --> 00:28:14,900
Let's say the sake of argument
that dark spirits are real.

370
00:28:14,908 --> 00:28:18,150
I would say your friend romano there
was a dark spirit long before that happened.

371
00:28:18,158 --> 00:28:20,423
- A living one?
- As these entities get stronger,

372
00:28:20,458 --> 00:28:22,772
they have the ability
to take over a weaker human.

373
00:28:22,777 --> 00:28:24,770
Literally take over
their bodies?

374
00:28:24,775 --> 00:28:26,911
In theory-- look, that's a picture of
some loser named romano

375
00:28:26,946 --> 00:28:30,321
with an evil heart and a weak will.,
But once the spirit got ahold of him

376
00:28:30,368 --> 00:28:32,490
all the negative energy
from that mass suicide--

377
00:28:32,498 --> 00:28:37,233
he was 100 times stronger. And then when
he died, he was released back into
the ether badder than ever.

378
00:28:37,997 --> 00:28:40,321
- And now?
- Now...

379
00:28:40,748 --> 00:28:42,831
regrouping
for a bigger bite.

380
00:28:42,836 --> 00:28:46,343
Maybe he's just sucking
up soul after soul and building more

381
00:28:46,347 --> 00:28:48,440
and more strength until the next
human being he takes over

382
00:28:48,446 --> 00:28:49,960
he could do some real
hurt to the world.

383
00:28:49,968 --> 00:28:53,472
And this guy's not gonna stop
until he destroys everything that's good.

384
00:28:54,286 --> 00:28:57,562
- You sound like a believer.
- I'd like to believe.

385
00:28:57,575 --> 00:29:02,060
I'd like to believe there's more than
this short rocket trip to the grave.

386
00:29:02,086 --> 00:29:04,083
I'd like to believe in
an afterlife.

387
00:29:05,088 --> 00:29:08,371
I believe in science. I need proof.
I need facts and figures.

388
00:29:08,415 --> 00:29:10,822
I can't just take it on faith
alone. And there lies the rub.

389
00:29:10,826 --> 00:29:14,721
No faith, no belief.

390
00:29:19,517 --> 00:29:24,273
I--I have
to plan breakfast now.

391
00:29:27,055 --> 00:29:29,922
Um...romano-- he didn't kill
anybody himself, did he?

392
00:29:30,335 --> 00:29:33,613
I mean, he just convinced them
to kill themselves.

393
00:29:33,618 --> 00:29:35,841
That also fits in
with the dark motif.

394
00:29:35,847 --> 00:29:37,831
In order for these things to win,
they have to take over a soul

395
00:29:37,845 --> 00:29:41,463
that acts with its own free will. They
have to cooperate in their own destruction.

396
00:30:15,076 --> 00:30:17,170
Hey, where the hell
have you been, kyle?

397
00:30:17,175 --> 00:30:21,020
- Well, I've been busy.
- I can see.

398
00:30:21,027 --> 00:30:24,593
Man, what's with you
and this chick...melinda?

399
00:30:25,085 --> 00:30:27,391
Like you're obsessed
with her.

400
00:30:28,848 --> 00:30:33,543
She and I--we have some
unfinished business.

401
00:30:35,315 --> 00:30:38,151
So the fact that romano
never physically killed anyone

402
00:30:38,167 --> 00:30:39,840
means that he has less power
than you thought.

403
00:30:39,846 --> 00:30:41,240
Means he has more power.

404
00:30:41,345 --> 00:30:45,922
Imagine being able to convince people--
100 of them-- to kill themselve

405
00:30:45,928 --> 00:30:48,670
- Gets in their heads, huh?
- No, he gets inside their souls.

406
00:30:48,676 --> 00:30:50,972
Makes them feel like
they're worthless, that they're bad.

407
00:30:50,976 --> 00:30:54,193
He poisons their spirits. And the weaker
they get, the stronger he gets.

408
00:30:54,547 --> 00:30:56,570
- He's doing this to andrea?
- Yeah, he's trying.

409
00:30:56,585 --> 00:31:00,300
And it makes me so frustrated, because
she's the only one who can turn him away.

410
00:31:00,305 --> 00:31:02,492
And I have to make her
understand that.

411
00:31:04,207 --> 00:31:06,282
- You don't know where she is?
- She said that she was going

412
00:31:06,285 --> 00:31:09,012
back to the beginning,
but the beginning of what?

413
00:31:09,016 --> 00:31:11,102
Your friendship?
The store?

414
00:31:13,135 --> 00:31:15,212
Wait a minute...

415
00:31:15,647 --> 00:31:20,343
I used to tell andrea all the time that
death isn't the end, it's the beginning.

416
00:31:20,807 --> 00:31:22,810
That's where she is.

417
00:31:22,816 --> 00:31:24,943
She went back
to where she died--

418
00:31:24,945 --> 00:31:26,961
where this began.

419
00:32:16,796 --> 00:32:19,092
- I can't cross over.
- Why not?

420
00:32:19,096 --> 00:32:21,091
Romano said I'd be punished.

421
00:32:21,096 --> 00:32:23,090
- For what?
- That night

422
00:32:23,096 --> 00:32:25,322
when mitch
came to the store

423
00:32:25,338 --> 00:32:27,353
and when you told him
I was dead.

424
00:32:28,816 --> 00:32:33,291
When I realized that was true--
that mitch was alive and I was dead...

425
00:32:35,168 --> 00:32:37,172
for just one minute

426
00:32:37,176 --> 00:32:41,792
I wanted to trade places.
I wanted to live so badly

427
00:32:42,027 --> 00:32:45,892
that I wished it was mitch who had
been killed by the plane and not me.

428
00:32:46,807 --> 00:32:49,060
I prayed for it.

429
00:32:49,078 --> 00:32:51,130
We were all in shock.

430
00:32:51,787 --> 00:32:56,533
But you have to talk to mitch. And he has
something that he has to say to you, too.

431
00:32:56,536 --> 00:33:01,380
My own brother,
and I wished him dead!

432
00:33:02,627 --> 00:33:05,001
I can't be forgiven for that.

433
00:33:05,006 --> 00:33:08,620
- Yes, you can.
- I don't want to be.

434
00:33:30,845 --> 00:33:34,792
I know you're packing,
but, I have to talk to you.

435
00:33:39,906 --> 00:33:41,950
I know this is a lot
to take in.

436
00:33:41,958 --> 00:33:44,891
- Ahh, you think?
- You tell me how well you know andrea.

437
00:33:44,897 --> 00:33:48,891
That she's not at rest, that
something's wrong. You can feel it.

438
00:33:49,097 --> 00:33:53,973
Did andrea know about this? That
you could... that you see the dead?

439
00:33:53,976 --> 00:33:57,212
Yes. I used to talk to her
about it all the time.

440
00:33:57,218 --> 00:33:59,402
I can't believe she never
said anything to you.

441
00:33:59,447 --> 00:34:01,300
- Did she believe you?
- Yes.

442
00:34:01,897 --> 00:34:04,581
She was so open
and curious.

443
00:34:05,566 --> 00:34:08,621
She had lots of questions,
always wanted to know more.

444
00:34:11,715 --> 00:34:15,311
That night...
in front of the store,

445
00:34:15,317 --> 00:34:17,951
when I saw you and you told me
what happened to andrea.

446
00:34:17,958 --> 00:34:20,370
Are you saying
that andrea was there?

447
00:34:20,558 --> 00:34:24,160
That you saw her? She
saw us, and she couldn't--

448
00:34:24,167 --> 00:34:26,862
she couldn't let me
know she was there?

449
00:34:26,895 --> 00:34:28,992
She was confused, mitch.

450
00:34:28,997 --> 00:34:32,663
She thought that you were the one that
was dead. It was hard for all of us.

451
00:34:32,667 --> 00:34:34,763
She's in a bad place.

452
00:34:34,767 --> 00:34:38,601
She can't cross over
into the light, and you're the reason.

453
00:34:38,617 --> 00:34:42,671
You have one last chance to do
something good for your sister.

454
00:34:50,146 --> 00:34:54,191
There's a lot of her in this place.
It'll help us to be here.

